    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for a Medium assurance, model risk level 3 assessment. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 single-configuration test is the regulatory submission standard and the model risk level does not compel multi-condition validation for this COU scope. All three primary QoIs satisfy both the E/uval < 1.96 and relative error < 10% acceptance criteria across N=11 specimens from two independent laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is credible for the stated COU.",
